21/04/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski met with Albanian counterpart Alfred Moisiu in Ohrid on Wednesday (20 April). 
The two leaders agreed they want to further develop bilateral relations, already described as very good. 
Moisiu and Crvenkovski stressed the importance of joint goals such as regional stability and Euro-Atlantic integration. 
Macedonian Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski made a parallel visit to Tirana Wednesday, where he and Albanian counterpart Pandeli Majko described bilateral military co-operation as a model for the whole region.
In other news, BiH and Macedonia sealed an agreement on the establishment of regular flights between the two countries, during BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic's visit to Skopje on Wednesday. 
Terzic and Macedonian counterpart Vlado Buckovski also discussed boosting bilateral trade and economic contacts. 
(Albanian News - 21/04/05; Albanian President Web site, Telma TV, Makfax, A1 TV, Fena, RTRS - 20/04/05)
